(30, 'plastic_reduce', 'plastic_reduce.png', 1, 'Don''t Drink Bottled Water', 'Approximately 25 percent of all bottled water is municipal tap water. New York''s water is so pure - it originates in streams upstate - that it does not need to be filtered.  It costs 49 cents a year to use New York City tap water, while it costs $1,400 a year to purchase bottled water.', 0, 0, 90, 0, 0, 17677, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2007-11-14 11:07:39'),
(30, 'plastic_reuse', 'plastic_reuse.png', 2, 'Refill Use Again', 'In 2006, Americans bought 50 billion water bottles - 167 for every person in the country. About 38 billion of those bottles ended up in a landfill.', 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 13258, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2007-11-14 11:07:39'),
(30, 'plastic_unsorted', 'plastic_unsorted.png', 2, 'Toss it in the Can', 'Nationwide, 2.5 million plastic bottles are thrown away every hour.', 0, 0, 99, 0, 17677, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2007-11-14 15:31:01'),
(30, 'plastic_sorted', 'paper_sorted.png', 1, 'Sort for Recycling', 'Nationwide, 25 percent of plastic bottles are recycled. Of all the glass, metal and plastics collected for recycling in the city, plastics make up about 13 percent. For residences, the city''s waste diversion rate for recycling is about 18 percent. The rate could be as a high as 36 percent, but 50 percent of materials that could be recycled are thrown out with the regular trash.', 0, 0, 97, 17677, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2007-11-14 16:10:01'),
