(150, 'compost_unsorted', 'compost_unsorted.png', 1, 'Toss it in the Can', 'Food waste accounts for about 22 percent of all residential garbage thrown away in NYC, with lawn clippings, dried leaves, branches and the like making up another 6 to 7.', 0, 0, 190, 0, 745000, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2007-11-14 15:32:01'),
(150, 'compost_sorted', 'compost_sorted.png', 2, 'Sort it for Curbside Pickup', 'The Department of Sanitation currently collects limited amounts of yard waste, fall leaves and Christmas trees. If New Yorkers went all out and composted food scraps and other compostables with our yard waste, up to 30 percent of the city''s refuse by some counts could avoid the landfill.', 0, 0, 192, 745000, 0, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2007-11-14 15:44:30'),
(150, 'compost_divert', 'compost_divert.png', 3, 'Put it in your Home Compost Bin', 'A number of organizations, including the Department of Sanitation, environmental groups and the city''s botanical gardens, offer instruction on how New Yorkers can compost safely in small spaces. Many community gardens also maintain compost bins.', 0, 0, 191, 0, 0, 745000, NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2007-11-12 17:04:06'),
